This paper deals with contract models and their relation to logic and game theory. The use of logic in contract modeling suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) sub-category. The paper also uses game theory, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of algorithms and strategies, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the practical applications of contract modeling, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category.
